attribution.changeMessage: According to 1900 U.S. Census he immigrated in 1860.

On 20Sep2015 CarolParrett indicated he immigrated to Utah in 1861.  Also, "Utah Mormon Pioneer Overland Travel Database, 1847-1868" on Family Search indicates George Sudbury Humpherys (born 19Apr1842 and died 19May1922) departed 17Jun1861 for Utah with the Edward Creighton Company.

On 03Oct2015 ConnieRSchreiner stated he "immigrated 19-20 Sep 1864 to Utah, United States. Evidently he went back to help other groups, this is his autobiographical story about that, including meeting and marrying his wife."  Also, "Utah Mormon Pioneer Overland Travel Database, 1847-1868" on Family Search indicates George Humpherys arrived in Utah on 20Sep1864 with the Joseph S. Rawlins Company.
1870 U.S. Census indicates Paris, Rich, Utah Territory. This was actually Paris, Bear Lake, Idaho, but the Mormon pioneers thought they were in Utah.

facts.value:
Sarah Jane Humpherys was born November 1, 1840 in Nottingham, England.  Her parents were
Thomas and Mary Humpherys.  Her family joined the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints in 1847.  In April 1853, the family embarked on the ship called "The Carmlus," and came to America
to join the Saints.  Her Father who had poor health weakened from the ship voyage and died.
This left Mary and six small children to go it alone.  In June, 1856, her family started across the
plains.  She and her small sons walked most of the way.  Sarah met James William Burbidge when they arrrived in Springville.  They were married on July 5, 1856.  They built a cabin with animal skins on the windows.  They had a family of five boys and 4 girls and all of them married in the temple.  James was a black smither.  Sarah had a rule in her home that no one would ever go away hungry.  She served homemade bread, butter  and gooseberry jam to many people in her
 diningroom.  One day James, was striken very suddenly, just after stepping from his own door.  Sarah did all in her power to revive him but he passed away on September 23, 1892, at the age of 55 years.  She and her famiy were heartbroken to loose him.  Sarah had a generous and loving nature, a keen sense of humor and enjoyed a good joke.  A good laugh is as beneficial as a good meal, she said.  She was always willing to assist in times of need or sickness.  She died on February 3, 1923, outliving her husband by thirty years.

Born in Skegway Nottinghamshire, England. Married Mary Sudbury on 26 Dec 1831 in Mansfield, Nottingham, England. His occupation on the England census is lace maker. He was converted to the LDS faith in England. Brought his family to America on the ship Camallis. Left Liverpool in 6 Apr 1853 and landed in New Orleans on the 7th of Jun 1853. Contracted dysentery and died on the 20th of Nov 1853. Death record lists him as a pauper leaving his oldest son John James to care for the family.
